1
00:00:17,940 --> 00:00:20,620
Mrs. Rabbit had four little bunnies.

2
00:00:21,780 --> 00:00:28,720
Their names were Mopsy, Flopsy, Cotton-tail, and Peter.

3
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:32,780
They lived in a hole under a tree.

4
00:00:38,120 --> 00:00:41,880
One day, Mrs. Rabbit said, "We need bread."

5
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:44,960
"I'll go into town to buy some."

6
00:00:46,580 --> 00:00:49,120
She grabbed her basket and an umbrella.

7
00:00:50,060 --> 00:00:52,300
Mrs. Rabbit looked at her bunnies.

8
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:56,020
"I will be back soon," she said.

9
00:00:57,020 --> 00:00:59,840
"Can we go outside?" asked Peter.

10
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:03,460
"Yes," said his mother.

11
00:01:06,540 --> 00:01:08,540
"But don't go into the farmer's garden."

12
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:11,960
"Your father went there."

13
00:01:12,010 --> 00:01:13,820
"And he never came home."

14
00:01:20,060 --> 00:01:22,500
"Okay, Mother," said the bunnies.

15
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:26,800
Mrs. Rabbit headed off to town.

16
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:36,560
The bunnies put on their jackets and shoes.

17
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:39,540
Then they went outside.

18
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,480
The four bunnies hopped down the path.

19
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:51,820
"Look over there!" said Mopsy.

20
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:54,600
"I see a blackberry bush!"

21
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:58,800
"Yum!" said Flopsy and Cotton-tail.

22
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:03,360
Flopsy, Mopsy, and Cotton-tail ran to the bush.

23
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:09,920
Peter's sisters started to pick blackberries.

24
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:17,240
"I don't want blackberries," Peter thought.

25
00:02:18,940 --> 00:02:21,300
"I'm going to the farmer's garden."

26
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:39,600
Peter hopped through the woods.

27
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:46,360
A path led to the farmer's gate.

28
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:58,680
Peter squeezed under the gate and looked around.

29
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:08,160
"I see green leaves everywhere!" said Peter.

30
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,920
Peter wandered through the garden.

31
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:29,190
He ate some lettuce.

32
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,980
He ate some green beans.

33
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,920
He ate some radishes.

34
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:50,950
"These vegetables are delicious!" said Peter.

35
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,680
"I'll eat some more."

36
00:03:58,260 --> 00:04:00,380
Then he hopped around a corner.

37
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:06,680
Peter gasped. "The farmer!"

38
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:11,040
The farmer gasped. "A rabbit!"

39
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,200
Peter ran.

40
00:04:14,140 --> 00:04:19,100
The farmer grabbed his rake and chased Peter.

41
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,540
"Stop, thief!" cried the farmer.

42
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:28,380
He swung his rake at Peter.

43
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:34,060
Peter ran as fast as he could. His heart beat fast.

44
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,920
He lost one shoe near the cabbages.

45
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,320
He lost his other shoe near the potatoes.

46
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:56,320
"Where's the gate?" cried Peter. He looked around.

47
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,500
Suddenly, he ran into a net.

48
00:05:02,380 --> 00:05:05,080
The big buttons on his jacket got caught.

49
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,880
"Ahh!" cried Peter.

50
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:15,160
He kicked and twisted, but it was no help.

51
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:20,460
"I'm stuck in the farmer's net!" cried Peter.

52
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,710
"Help!" cried Peter.

53
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:48,120
"I'm stuck in this net!"

54
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:53,080
Some birds flew over to Peter.

55
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,920
They tried to help him.

56
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:03,960
"Don't give up!" called one bird.

57
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:08,060
"Keep trying to get free!"

58
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:15,320
"Take off your jacket!" shouted another.

59
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:18,140
Peter stopped crying.

60
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:22,180
Quickly, Peter slipped out of his jacket.

61
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,340
Now he was free.

62
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:32,120
But the farmer was still chasing him.

63
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:35,440
Peter ran away fast.

64
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:39,180
"Get back here!" cried the farmer.

65
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:46,340
Peter dashed into a shed.

66
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,440
It was filled with garden tools.

67
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:56,540
Peter leaped into a watering can.

68
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:05,340
The can was filled with icy water.

69
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,240
"Brr!" said Peter.

70
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:08,480
The farmer rushed into the shed.

71
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:13,620
"Where is that rabbit?" said the farmer.

72
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,220
Peter shivered.

73
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,880
He heard the farmer moving things around.

74
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:29,260
"Where are you, rabbit?" muttered the farmer.

75
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,600
The farmer's footsteps were close now.

76
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,960
"Uh-oh," whispered Peter.

77
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:39,520
He felt a tickle in his nose.

78
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,400
The tickle grew worse.

79
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,180
"Ah-choo!" Peter sneezed.

80
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,820
Peter jumped out of the watering can.

81
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:21,140
"Hey!" cried the farmer.

82
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:30,720
Peter ran and ran.

83
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:39,200
Finally, the farmer stopped chasing him.

84
00:08:45,980 --> 00:08:47,880
Now Peter was lost.

85
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,000
"Where's the gate?" he asked a mouse.

86
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,240
But the mouse ran away.

87
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:10,500
Suddenly, Peter gasped. "A cat!"

88
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:14,240
The cat was watching fish in the pond.

89
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,500
She didn't see Peter.

90
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,000
"Whew!" whispered Peter.

91
00:09:23,260 --> 00:09:25,100
He quietly slipped away.

92
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:34,160
"I must find the gate," said Peter.

93
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:39,680
Scritch, scratch! Peter heard a noise.

94
00:09:43,460 --> 00:09:46,020
He climbed onto a wheelbarrow to see.

95
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:49,940
The farmer was working in the onion patch.

96
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:56,140
Scritch, scratch!

97
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:58,400
Then Peter saw something else.

98
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,660
"The gate!" he cried.

99
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:09,520
Peter shot across the garden.

100
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,320
The farmer chased him. "Stop, rabbit!"

101
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:20,000
But Peter was too fast.

102
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:23,900
He squeezed under the gate and ran home.

103
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:35,940
Mrs. Rabbit scolded Peter. "Naughty rabbit!"

104
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:39,080
"You lost your jacket and shoes!"

105
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,740
The other bunnies ate bread and blackberries.

106
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:51,640
But Peter didn't get any.

107
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,920
Peter sneezed.

108
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:08,340
Mrs. Rabbit gave him medicine.

109
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:17,560
Then she sent him to bed.

